[normal]1.3
[normal]We own and manage over
[normal] 28,000 homes across London and the South East of England. We focus on core social housing activities offe
[normal]ring a range of housing options. 
[normal]A
[normal]HL
[normal] also 
[normal]provides 1,150 private rented sector (PRS) homes for use 
[normal]as temporary accommodation (TA).
[normal] We manage these homes through a trading entity called Avenue Lettings. We lease homes from 500 individual landlords and work with 18 local authorities
[normal] (LA
[normal]) 
[normal]to
[normal] provide great quality self contained homes for homeless families.  We’ve been providing this ser
[normal]vice for over 11 years. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]AHL support the prin
[normal]ciples behind Universal Credit. We can see the Government has made
[normal] significant progress in designing a system to help ease the transition from benefits to work. We recognise the new system will be effective for
[normal] the majority of claimants but have concerns about some of the more vulnerable benefit claimants. We therefore welcome the opportunity to submit a response to the select committee.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Over the next three years 70% of our residents will face significant chang
[normal]es to their income. They’ll be managing increasingly tight budgets and we anticipate an impact on both the cost of rent collection and the amount of arrears.
[normal]&#xa0;
