[normal]4.0[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]We’re working with residents who are under occupying properties to use mutual exchange where possible to minimise their financial risk. 
[normal]We’ve also encouraged people who are overcrowded to contact us to help with 
[normal]the matching exercise.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We’ve produced a suite of leaflets/guides on how to open a bank account, find a job, avoid loan sharks and reduce energy bills.
[normal] We produce a quarterly newsletter
[normal], have a regular presence at resident involvement events 
[normal]and have 
[normal]also uploaded a dvd on welfare reform to ensure residents are completely up to speed on the changes.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Our data is crucial. We’ve actively used our 
[normal]Customer Relationship Management (
[normal]CRM
[normal])
[normal] system to capture contact on welfare reform.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We’ve also made our staf
[normal]f more accessible. Since the welfare reform changes, we’ve added 24 extra contact hours per week for customers to
[normal] speak to an Income Officer or a Lettings Co-ordinator managing a homeless client.
[normal] We can be contacted from 8-8 Monday to Friday and 9-1 on Sat
[normal]urdays.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Internally, we’ve changed our working practices to ensure greater impact. For example, we make time f
[normal]or outbound telephone campaigns and carry out visits outside before 9am and after 5pm, as well as Saturday mornings.
[normal] By groups of staff taking to 
[normal]the phones together
[normal] or visits
[normal], we can create a real energy and keep employees motivated.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In-bound calls are answered within 15 seconds and customer satisfaction with our income team
[normal] &amp; private sector leasing team
[normal] currently stands at 98%. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We’ve written ou
[normal]t twice in the last six months to every customer who hasn’t got a bank account based on our data collection exercise. We’ve created a grid of 
[normal]available bank accounts for staff to guide customers. We’ve also written a ‘How to Get a Bank Account’ leaflet whi
[normal]ch is sent with arrears letter
[normal]s as well as working
[normal] closely with a number of credit unions.
