[normal]Implications to AHL regarding service charges[bold]4.1
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.2
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.3
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]4.4
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]We have over 18,000 service charge payers. All are affected in some way by the introduction of Universal Credit.  
[normal]Negative implications could affect us as landlords in two ways
[normal]: 
[normal]Current legisla
[normal]tion allows us to depreciate the cost of
[normal] repairs and replacement of lifts
[normal]. 
[normal]Under revised 
[normal]DWP guidance
[normal] this won’t continue to happen.
[normal] The impact
[normal] means a potential annual loss of 
[normal]£550,000
[normal]. Service charges could be increased to cover this, but with many resid
[normal]ents affected by welfare changes, ultimately we’ll have to cover the loss through bad debt provision. This has
[normal] an adverse effect on our business plan and therefore our ability to build new homes. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In some flats, particularly high rise we have responsibility for window cleaning. DWP guidance says we will not be able to charge for cleaning relating to ground floor flats. 
[normal]Significant timely and costly work has to be undertaken for us to 
[normal]change all lega
[normal]l agreements with residents’
[normal]. Without this residents will
[normal] be paying for 
[normal]services they don’t receive.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The guidance also fails to take account of the legal agreements with tenants, including leaseholders. These constrain the options available to both us
[normal] and the tenant. Apportionments for charges are set out in leases and tenancy agreements.  It’s a contract to pay us charges due. So, those in flats will have to make their Universal Credit payment stretch further to cover the cost of non eligible charges 
[normal]which they have no choice but to receive.
[normal] Ultimately as a landlord we’ll be at a financial loss as bad debt is incurred.
[normal]&#xa0;
