[normal]This only works with buy in and support from LA.
[normal] A blanket approach of discharge into the PRS could lead to a ‘revolving door’ of homelessness for some families, again leading 
[normal]to a
[normal] higher B&amp;B bill/ cost to public purse. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Recommendations[bold]&#xa0;[bold]We reiterate that we agree in principle the aim of welfare reform /universal credit /direct payments – The 
[normal]unintended consequence of direct payments is likely to be higher costs to housing providers, negative impact on credit ratings and fewer new homes bu
[normal]ilt, as mentioned above. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]If we and other providers are unable to continue to secure temporary accommodation, Local Authorities will have to use Bed and Breakfast accommodation more. This costs more, both to the public purse and in terms of impact on vulnerable homeless families.
